# PharmaSoft Project Structure Documentation

## Root Directory

### Configuration Files
- `firebase.json` - Firebase configuration for emulators, hosting, and services
- `firestore.rules` - Security rules for Firestore database
- `firestore.indexes.json` - Indexes configuration for Firestore queries
- `storage.rules` - Security rules for Firebase Storage
- `package.json` - Node.js dependencies and scripts for the root project
- `.env` - Environment variables for the project (not committed to version control)

### Backend Files
- `functions/` - Firebase Cloud Functions directory
  - `index.js` - Entry point for Cloud Functions, contains simplified endpoint implementations
  - `package.json` - Node.js dependencies for Cloud Functions

## Frontend Directory (`frontend/`)

### Configuration Files
- `frontend/package.json` - Node.js dependencies and scripts for the React frontend
- `frontend/.env` - Environment variables for the React app, contains Firebase configuration
- `frontend/public/` - Static files for the React app
  - `index.html` - HTML template for the React app
  - `manifest.json` - Web manifest for Progressive Web App features
  - `favicon.ico` - Website favicon
  - `robots.txt` - Instructions for search engine crawlers

### Source Files (`frontend/src/`)
- `index.js` - Entry point for the React application, initializes Firebase
- `App.js` - Main component that sets up routing and providers
- `App.simple.js` - Simplified version of App.js for testing Firebase connectivity (can be removed)
- `index.css` - Global CSS styles
- `firebase.js` - Duplicated Firebase initialization (can be removed, using services/firebase.js instead)
- `i18n.js` - Internationalization configuration
- `i18n-mock.js` - Mock internationalization for testing (can be removed)
- `reportWebVitals.js` - Performance monitoring utility

### Components Directory (`frontend/src/components/`)
- `ErrorBoundary.js` - React error boundary for catching runtime errors
- `Loading.js` - Loading spinner component
- `NetworkStatus.js` - Component to display network connection status

### Context Providers (`frontend/src/contexts/`)
- `AuthContext.js` - Authentication context provider and hooks
- `NotificationContext.js` - Notification system context provider and hooks

### Configuration (`frontend/src/config/`)
- `firebaseConfig.js` - Firebase configuration variables and emulator settings

### Services (`frontend/src/services/`)
- `firebase.js` - Firebase initialization and service exports
- `authService.js` - Old authentication service (replaced by firebase.js, can be removed)

### API Layer (`frontend/src/api/`)
- `authApi.js` - Old API for authentication with Flask backend (can be removed)
- Other API files may be present and should be reviewed

### Pages (`frontend/src/pages/`)
- `Homepage.js` - Landing page component
- `About.js` - About page component
- `Support.js` - Customer support page
- `FAQs.js` - Frequently asked questions page
- `Login.js` - User login page
- `Signup.js` - User registration page
- `NotFound.js` - 404 page
- `PharmacistsDashboard.js` - Dashboard for pharmacists
- `Admin.js` - Admin dashboard

### Internationalization (`frontend/src/locales/`)
- `en/translation.json` - English translations
- `es/translation.json` - Spanish translations
- `fr/translation.json` - French translations

### Styles (`frontend/src/styles/`)
- `app.css` - Styles for the main application
- `login.css` - Styles for authentication pages
- `notifications.css` - Styles for notification components

## Unused Files (Can Be Removed)
1. `frontend/src/firebase.js` - Redundant with `services/firebase.js`
2. `frontend/src/i18n-mock.js` - Testing mock for i18n
3. `frontend/src/App.simple.js` - Simplified testing version
4. `frontend/src/api/authApi.js` - Old Flask API integration
5. `frontend/src/services/authService.js` - Replaced by firebase.js
6. Any files related to the Flask backend

## Firebase Emulator Files
- `firestore-debug.log` - Debug logs for Firestore emulator (should be in .gitignore)
- Other emulator logs may be present and should be added to .gitignore

## Database Structure

### Firestore Collections
- `users` - User profiles and related data
  - Document ID: User UID from Firebase Auth
  - Fields: displayName, email, role, createdAt, updatedAt, etc.

## Authentication System
The application uses Firebase Authentication with the following providers:
- Email/Password authentication
- Google authentication
- Potential for Facebook authentication (code present but may not be fully implemented)

## Application Features
1. User Authentication (login, signup, password reset)
2. Internationalization with multiple languages
3. Protected routes for authenticated users
4. Pharmacist dashboard for job management
5. Network status monitoring
6. Error boundary for catching runtime errors
7. Notification system for user feedback

## Development Environment
- React frontend using Create React App
- Firebase emulators for local development
- i18next for internationalization 